claude
______

# Disco Limerick

There once was a dancer named Joe,
Whose moves made the disco floor glow.
With sequins so bright,
He danced through the night,
While the DJ kept beats nice and slow.

His platform shoes reached to the sky,
As under the ball he would fly.
The Hustle, his game,
Brought him disco fame,
Making wallflowers wither and sigh.

When the disco era declined,
Joe's spandex was neatly confined.
But on special nights,
He turns on the lights,
For the boogie he left behind.

