**Disco Delight**  

There once was a dance floor so bright,  
Where folks boogied all through the night.  
With mirror balls high,  
They’d reach for the sky—  
Oh, disco was pure dynamite!  

A man wore his bell-bottoms tight,  
While spinning under neon light.  
With a "Stayin’ Alive" groove,  
He just couldn’t move—  
His platform shoes gave him a fright!  

The DJ played funky and loud,  
The bass shook the whole dancing crowd.  
But when power went dead,  
They just air-guitared instead—  
Disco fans? Truly so proud!

